To Art:<br>
     I'm glad you and Doc Del brought up the amnesty program.  How could our government forgive men who ran away from this country.  I believe it forgave those men who went to Canada? Right?  I guess it still burns me up.  In the 70's this country didn't even want to help the vet yet gave amnesty for those that ran.  Your right, it doesn't have seem to created any healing just hard feelings.  In the mind of open discussion, I am curious.  Is there anyone out there that feels this was a good move?  I would like to hear your side.  One last thing for Art, Doc Del or any of the other guys-Does anyone know how many people went to prison for violation of draft laws??  I don't think is was many?  Amnesty-what an idea!!
